Good, the PoC file is created. Now let me refine it based on a deeper understanding of the vulnerability. Looking at the code again:

In `xmlAddIDSafe` (lines 2546-2558):
```c
} else {
    ret = xmlHashLookup(table, value);
    if (ret != NULL) {
        /*
         * Update the attribute to make entities work.
         */
        if (ret->attr != NULL) {
            ret->attr->id = NULL;  // This clears the old attr's id pointer
            ret->attr = attr;       // This assigns new attr
        }
        attr->atype = XML_ATTRIBUTE_ID;
        attr->id = ret;
        return(0);
    }
}
```

The issue is that when the same ID is encountered twice (once from the entity definition and once from the expanded entity), the old attribute's `id` field is set to NULL, but if that attribute has already been freed (in streaming mode where attributes can be copied from entities), this causes a use-after-free.

